  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "To import your Gmail contacts into Skype, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Export your Gmail contacts:**\n   - Open Gmail and click on the Google apps grid (icon with nine dots) in the upper right corner.\n   - Select \"Contacts.\"\n   - On the left side, click \"Export.\"\n   - Choose \"Google CSV\" format and click \"Export.\"\n   - Save the file to your computer.\n\n2. **Import contacts into Skype:**\n   - Open Skype and sign in to your account.\n   - Click on your profile picture.\n   - Select \"Settings\" or \"Manage contacts.\"\n   - Click on \"Import contacts.\"\n   - Choose the Gmail option and follow any additional prompts to allow access to your Google account.\n   - If prompted, select the .CSV file you downloaded earlier.\n  \nWhen the process is complete, your Gmail contacts should be available in Skype. Note that Skype and Gmail periodically update their interfaces, so steps may vary slightly. Always refer to the latest help documentation if you encounter any issues.",
